    "millsfield:images_texts": [
      "AIRLINES",
      "TWA-Trans World Airlines, Inc.\nLockheed 1649A Starliner\nA completely redesigned version of the successful line of\nConstellation aircraft, the Starliner was the first to provide\nTrans-Atlantic non-stop capability in both directions under\nall conditions.\nA truly ultra-long\nrange airliner,\nalso\noperated Polar flights between California and Europe, and\nstill holds the record for the longest non-stop commercial\npassenger flight in terms of time aloft. On October 2, 1957,\nTWA's inaugural westbound trip landed in San Francisco 23\nhours and 19 minutes after taking off from London. TWA\nreferred to the Starliner as the \"Jetstream\" and operated\ntwenty-five of them. The last was delivered less than a year\nbefore the first jet, and as a result the Jetstream fleet carried\npassengers only four years before being converted to cargo\naircraft. The last was retired in 1967.\nXerox P933)\nfor\nAGS\nPublished by Aviation World, Inc., P.O. Box 188, Bethel, Conn. 06801 U.S.A.\nL-028\n81594-D\npost card\n2001. 082.076"
    ],
